---
/**
 * context-engineering 0009 · Figure 1 — the hero "three governors" diagram.
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from
 * docs/context-engineering/lessons/0009-context-caching-ordering-and-security.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption incl. the footnote <sup>). It lives as an .astro
 * component, NOT inline in the MDX, because MDX's JSX parser is unreliable with
 * raw inline SVG that uses kebab-case attributes (text-anchor, font-size,
 * stroke-width, marker-end, …). In an .astro file the SVG is plain HTML, so it
 * renders byte-for-byte.
 *
 * The source page defined the arrowhead markers ONCE in a shared <defs> block at
 * the top of the document <body> (ids: arw, arwG, arwR, arwM). The MDX has no
 * such shared block, so the markers this figure references (arw, arwG, arwR) are
 * inlined into its own <defs>.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 300"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Three production concerns layered over one context pipeline: caching for cost, ordering for accuracy, security for safety."
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arw"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#6b675f"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwG"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#2f5d3a"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwR"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#9a2417"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <!-- the pipeline spine -->
        <rect
            x="40"
            y="130"
            width="120"
            height="44"
            rx="8"
            fill="#f6eef7"
            stroke="#b5179e"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="100" y="150" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >Assemble</text
        >
        <text x="100" y="165" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f"
            >prompt + retrieved</text
        >
        <rect
            x="260"
            y="130"
            width="120"
            height="44"
            rx="8"
            fill="#f1eef2"
            stroke="#b5179e"
            stroke-width="2"></rect>
        <text x="320" y="150" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#b5179e"
            >Context window</text
        >
        <text x="320" y="165" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f"
            >one fixed budget</text
        >
        <rect
            x="480"
            y="130"
            width="120"
            height="44"
            rx="8"
            fill="#f6eef7"
            stroke="#b5179e"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="540" y="150" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >LLM answer</text
        >
        <text x="540" y="165" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f">f(context)</text>
        <line x1="160" y1="152" x2="256" y2="152" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <line x1="380" y1="152" x2="476" y2="152" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>

        <!-- three concern badges -->
        <rect
            x="40"
            y="34"
            width="170"
            height="62"
            rx="10"
            fill="#e9f3ec"
            stroke="#2f5d3a"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="125" y="54" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >1 · Caching = cost</text
        >
        <text x="125" y="72" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >stable prefix first</text
        >
        <text x="125" y="86" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >reuse, don't reprocess</text
        >
        <rect
            x="235"
            y="34"
            width="170"
            height="62"
            rx="10"
            fill="#eef2f7"
            stroke="#1f3a5a"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="320" y="54" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" font-weight="700" fill="#1f3a5a"
            >2 · Ordering = accuracy</text
        >
        <text x="320" y="72" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >edges get read</text
        >
        <text x="320" y="86" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >middle gets skimmed</text
        >
        <rect
            x="430"
            y="34"
            width="170"
            height="62"
            rx="10"
            fill="#fbecec"
            stroke="#9a2417"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="515" y="54" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
            >3 · Security = safety</text
        >
        <text x="515" y="72" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >untrusted data</text
        >
        <text x="515" y="86" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >ACL in the query</text
        >

        <line
            x1="125"
            y1="96"
            x2="105"
            y2="128"
            stroke="#2f5d3a"
            stroke-dasharray="3 3"
            marker-end="url(#arwG)"></line>
        <line
            x1="320"
            y1="96"
            x2="320"
            y2="128"
            stroke="#1f3a5a"
            stroke-dasharray="3 3"
            marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <line
            x1="515"
            y1="96"
            x2="535"
            y2="128"
            stroke="#9a2417"
            stroke-dasharray="3 3"
            marker-end="url(#arwR)"></line>

        <text x="320" y="216" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" font-style="italic" fill="#b5179e"
            >Same pipeline you already built — now made cheap, accurate, and safe to run in
            production.</text
        >
        <text x="320" y="240" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >Lessons 1–8 chose WHAT to retrieve. This lesson governs HOW it's laid out and trusted.</text
        >
        <text x="320" y="276" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >Caching and ordering both want the query LAST — they agree, not fight.</text
        >
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        The final layer. You already know how to <em>select</em> context; production adds three governors:
        <b>cost</b> (cache the stable prefix), <b>accuracy</b> (place content where the model reads it),
        and <b>safety</b> (trust nothing retrieved, scope every query).<sup
            ><a href="#s1" id="r1b">1</a></sup
        >
    </figcaption>
</figure>
